com.google.code.gwt.database.client
Class SQLTransaction

java.lang.Object
  com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject
      com.google.code.gwt.database.client.SQLTransaction

public class SQLTransaction
extends JavaScriptObject

Represents a transaction as started by a Database.transaction(TransactionCallback) or Database.readTransaction(TransactionCallback) call.

You can use this class to invoke SQL statements by means of executeSql(String, Object[]). Instances of this class also mark the boundaries of a transaction.

See Also:
W3C Web Database - SQLTransaction

Method Detail

executeSql

public final void executeSql(String sqlStatement,
                             Object[] arguments)
Executes the provided sqlStatement with the specified arguments.

The SQL is executed in a SQLite3 database. Please see the SQL Language Reference for its capabilities.

Because this method doesn't specify any callback, whenever a database error occurs the transaction will be rolled-back (as if a StatementCallback.onFailure(SQLTransaction, SQLError) callback returns true).

Parameters:
sqlStatement - the SQL statement to execute, containing "?" placeholders for the arguments
arguments - the arguments to fit in the placeholders of the sqlStatement (could be null)
See Also:
W3C Web Database - SQLTransaction - executeSql, SQLite3 SQL Language Reference

executeSql

public final void executeSql(String sqlStatement,
                             Object[] arguments,
                             StatementCallback<?> callback)
Executes the provided sqlStatement with the specified arguments.

The SQL is executed in a SQLite3 database. Please see the SQL Language Reference for its capabilities.

Parameters:
sqlStatement - the SQL statement to execute, containing "?" placeholders for the arguments
arguments - the arguments to fit in the placeholders of the sqlStatement (could be null)
callback - the callback for handling errors and the resultset of the SQL statement
See Also:
